summary: This document is a chain of emails from June 2019 arranging a conference call to discuss victim interviews in the Epstein case. It involves FBI personnel from the Violent Crimes Task Force and Victim Services Division coordinating scheduling.

events.title: Conference call on Epstein victim interviews
events.description: An unclassified conference call was scheduled for 2 pm Eastern Time to discuss victim interviews in the Epstein case.

keyFacts: A conference call was scheduled for June 28, 2019, to discuss victim interviews in the Epstein case.
The coordination involved the FBI NY Criminal Division Violent Crimes Task Force and the FBI Victim Services Division Child Victim Services Unit.
The document indicates ongoing investigative activity regarding victim interviews in mid-2019.
